{
  "texts": [
    "By deallocating and reinitializing ancillas in |0⟩, this kind of idling time can be minimized, and the impacts of noise can be made minimal.",
    "Moreover, idling of logical qubits is also costly in faulttolerant architectures, which require continuous error correction even when no gates are being performed.",
    "Each round of error correction requires a set of parity check circuits and measurements, followed by a nontrivial classical decoding calculation, all of which contribute to the overall energy expenditure of the computation.Another feature of our constructions is that they are garbage-free.",
    "This contrasts with some previous work (e.g., [23,24]), which perform a relaxed version of the QSP task, where, instead of preparing the nqubit state |ψ⟩ from Eq.",
    "(1), one aims to prepare an (n + a)-qubit state |Ψ⟩ given by|Ψ⟩ = 1 ∥x∥ 2 n -1 i=0 (x i |i⟩ ⊗ |garbage i ⟩)."
  ]
}